ğŸ“ Text Summarization using T5 and Hugging Face

This project demonstrates automatic text summarization using T5 (Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer), a powerful NLP model by Google AI. The implementation is done in Google Colab using the Hugging Face Transformers library, along with supporting tools like SACREMOSES for tokenization. It covers both extractive and abstractive summarization techniques.

ğŸš€ What is T5?

T5 stands for Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer. It's a transformer-based model designed to solve all NLP tasks using a text-to-text framework, where both input and output are treated as plain text. For example, to summarize a document, the input would be:

ğŸ”§ Key Features of T5:

Unified approach to NLP tasks (translation, summarization, Q&A, etc.)
Pre-trained on a massive dataset, then fine-tuned for specific tasks
Achieves state-of-the-art performance in multiple NLP benchmarks
Highly flexible and adaptable for custom datasets and use-cases

ğŸ“š Dataset Used: XSum

The XSum (Extreme Summarization) dataset contains news articles paired with one-sentence human-written summaries. It is designed to push the boundaries of abstractive summarization, where the goal is to generate novel sentences capturing the core message of the original document.

